00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:04,437
Anyway, I'm just glad that you like it.

238
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:09,400
[Komi grunting]

239
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:13,487
Uh, well,

240
00:10:14,196 --> 00:10:17,908
that's, uh, a piece of, uh, candy.

241
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:20,077
[Komi gasping]

242
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,627
[both grunting]

243
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:29,962
So, um, sorry.

244
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:31,839
I'm gonna go home now.

245
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:35,343
I don't wanna bother you
any longer, you know?

246
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,178
Especially since it's a weekend!

247
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,596
[Hitohito chuckling nervously]

248
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,480
[Komi grunting]

249
00:10:58,783 --> 00:11:01,494
[Komi sniffing]

250
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,412
[Komi sighing]

251
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:05,122
[narrator] <i>It smelled good.</i>

252
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,168
{\an8}- [Maeda] Sato, can you hold this for me?
- Yeah, sure!

253
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,045
[Hitohito sighing]

254
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:12,296
Komi?

255
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:15,508
Is it okay to use this towel
to wipe off the desks?

256
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:17,802
Huh?

257
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,887
[indistinct chatter]

258
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:22,556
Uh, Komi?

259
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:24,225
Die!

260
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,852
{\an8}ROLL

261
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:32,441
Let's play Eraser Drop!

262
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:33,359
[Hitohito] Huh? Why?

263
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,902
[narrator] <i>Eraser Drop.</i>

264
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:37,321
<i>An eraser is a physical object
created by humans</i>

265
00:11:37,321 --> 00:11:39,240
<i>who leveraged
their entire body of knowledge</i>

266
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,908
<i>built over the history of humankind...</i>

267
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:43,744
You flick your eraser, and if your
opponent's eraser drops to the floor,

268
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:44,662
you win.

269
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,914
[Makeru] It's my turn to take the stage.

270
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:49,917
[narrator] <i>They're using Tadano's desk
as the battlefield.</i>

271
00:11:49,917 --> 00:11:52,169
- And set!
- [announcer] <i>Round one.</i>

272
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:54,338
<i>Fight!</i>

273
00:11:54,338 --> 00:11:55,256
BEAM

274
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:57,174
Victory goes to who makes the first move!

275
00:11:57,174 --> 00:11:59,218
Whoa! She's squishing down on the eraser,

276
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:01,178
which makes the eraser stick to the desk!

277
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:03,431
{\an8}The "Barricade" move!

278
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,766
{\an8}[Chushaku] <i>If you do this,
other players will badmouth you.</i>

279
00:12:05,766 --> 00:12:07,101
[music stops]

280
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:08,936
[Makeru grunting]

281
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,771
[Najimi] You can go next, Komi.

282
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:14,191
PLINK

283
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:15,109
[Najimi] Stalling!

284
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:18,195
She didn't move her eraser so
her opponents would make a mistake first?

285
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:21,073
Great move!
A perfect fit for your eraser unit!

286
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:23,284
[narrator] <i>Actually,
her hand just slipped.</i>

287
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:25,327
Well, it's my turn now.

288
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:28,247
- [Najimi roaring]
- [intense music playing]

289
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:33,752
[music fades]

290
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:35,880
[narrator] <i>Out of bounds.
Najimi disqualified.</i>

291
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,465
[Makeru] Now, it's my turn.

292
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:39,633
- [Makeru roaring]
- [intense music playing]

293
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,302
Her eraser's barricaded!

294
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:43,554
She flicked it too hard!

295
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:47,391
[narrator] <i>Out of bounds.
Makeru Yadano disqualified.</i>

296
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,309
[music stops]

297
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:49,727
Tadano, it's your turn.

298
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:51,103
[Hitohito groaning]

299
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,855
FANTASTIC ERASER MOON

300
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,441
[Hitohito sighing]

301
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:58,360
- ZAFU II
- KOMI'S ERASER

302
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,780
- [Tadano roaring]
- [intense music playing]

303
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,160
[Komi gasping]

304
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,203
[music stops]

305
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:11,499
[narrator] <i>Hitohito Tadano
has been disqualified.</i>

306
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,083
<i>As a result, Komi wins.</i>

307
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,668
All right! Next game!

308
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:16,337
[Nakanaka] The time has come.

309
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:19,215
{\an8}I know you want to see my awesome skills!

310
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:22,510
[announcer] <i>New challenger, Nakanaka!</i>

311
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,095
- [Yamai] Don't worry about a thing, Komi!
- [Nakanaka] You!

312
00:13:25,095 --> 00:13:26,889
[announcer] <i>New challenger, Yamai.</i>

313
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:30,726
I'll defend your eraser to the death.
Even if I have to sacrifice my own life!

314
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:33,854
Ha! That's redundant.
Like saying my headache hurts.

315
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:35,481
- Huh?
- Ah?

316
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:38,484
Najimi, the phoenix, that's me!

317
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:40,110
[announcer] <i>Round two.</i>

318
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:41,111
<i>Fight!</i>

319
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:43,364
[all roaring]

320
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:44,698
Oh look.

321
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,116
Hey, what's going on?

322
00:13:46,116 --> 00:13:48,452
They're playing Eraser Drop!
I wanna play too!

323
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:50,371
Huh? They're not playing the game right.

324
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:52,373
I thought players
are supposed to take turns?

325
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:54,375
- [boy] I wanna play too!
- I wanna play!

326
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,669
{\an8}The three of us reserve the third battle.

327
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:57,586
[all exclaiming]

328
00:13:57,586 --> 00:14:00,339
{\an8}<i>[Hitohito] Why does everyone wanna play
Eraser Drop so bad?</i>

329
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,424
[announcer] <i>Witness this fierce battle</i>

330
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:04,843
<i>that turns
all other Eraser Drop battles into dust!</i>

331
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:07,763
They've taken the concept
of taking turns and...

332
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:09,014
[Hitohito] <i>And that's good?</i>

333
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:09,932
All right!

334
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:13,102
Round two, battle three,
will take place on this desk over here!

335
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:15,771
- The come-back match is over here!
- [Hitohito] <i>A tournament?</i>

336
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:19,775
[Makoto] <i>I ended up joining a game somehow
without knowing how to play!</i>

337
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:22,528
<i>What am I gonna do?
I've never played Eraser Drop before!</i>

338
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,822
<i>Why are there so many people here?</i>

339
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:28,534
[Makoto grunting]

340
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:29,994
[Naruse grunting]

341
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:32,121
I'll show you
what a real eraser battle looks like.

342
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,707
[Makoto snarling, roaring]

343
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:36,625
[intense music playing]

344
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:42,131
[crowd cheering]

345
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:43,966
[Naruse groaning]

346
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:44,884
[Chushaku] <i>It's okay.</i>

347
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,469
Hey! Look at that desk over there!

348
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:48,846
[Nakanaka groaning]

349
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,348
Nakanaka is starting to get worn out!

350
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:53,100
She overexerted her finger!

351
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,602
[Mono] She has a weak constitution!

352
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:56,478
Huh? Huh?

353
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,896
[Najimi cackling]

354
00:14:57,896 --> 00:15:00,232
[Taisei] They powered up their finger!

355
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:02,735
That's cheating! That's cheating, Najimi!

356
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:05,738
Winning is all that matters! Let's go!

357
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,989
[Najimi screaming]

358
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:07,990
Now's her chance!

359
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:09,658
[all] It's Komi's turn!

360
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:21,003
FLICK

361
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:23,505
[dramatic music playing]

362
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:32,264
[all] She did it! Woo-hoo!

363
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:34,516
WOOO!

364
00:15:34,516 --> 00:15:36,518
[crowd cheering]

365
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,271
[Hitohito grunting]

366
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:41,523
- Does this look right?
- You can do it!

367
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,566
- [boy] Wow!
- Yes.

368
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:43,525
[Yuji] I knew it.

369
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:46,528
Hey! Is it finally my turn to battle now?

370
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:49,031
[Ushiroda] Uh, hey! You can't do that!

371
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,283
This is so tough.

372
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:53,035
[Makeru seething]

373
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,328
Yeah!

374
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:55,913
[Toshio roaring]

375
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:58,415
Yay! On to round three!

376
00:15:58,415 --> 00:16:00,417
[Onemine chuckling] Okay. That was fun.

377
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:02,670
I'm coming back!

378
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,546
- [boy] I'm playing next!
- [girl] No, I am!

379
00:16:04,546 --> 00:16:05,506
[girl 2] I am!

380
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:06,757
[Hitohito chuckling]

381
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:08,676
{\an8}Komi, so about round two. Uh...

382
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:10,344
[Komi grunting]

383
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:12,846
[Hitohito] Huh?

384
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:14,598
Komi?

385
00:16:14,598 --> 00:16:15,641
[Komi gasping]

386
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:19,520
{\an8}Hey, uh, are you okay?

387
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,313
{\an8}Gosh, are you feeling sick?

388
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:25,234
"Sorry. I'm okay. I'm fine."

389
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:26,151
I see.

390
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:33,909
[rain pattering]

391
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:35,160
All right, Tadano.

392
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,663
I'm double-booked. Gotta go. Bye!

393
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:38,914
Uh, hey, you!

394
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:45,045
Comrade, we shall meet
on the battlefield another day.

395
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:48,382
Well, I... I thank you so much
for all the fun I had today.

396
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,384
- Bye-bye Komi!
- Komi, give me a goodbye kiss!

397
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:51,343
WHACK

398
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:54,263
- See you later! Sleep well, Ren.
- [Agari laughing]

399
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:09,153
Uh...

400
00:17:24,501 --> 00:17:25,461
[Komi grunting]

401
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:27,796
[Hitohito] I see it started raining.

402
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:30,007
Do you have an umbrella?

403
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:33,218
{\an8}"I have a folding umbrella."

404
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:34,511
{\an8}Oh, good.

405
00:17:35,095 --> 00:17:36,388
I brought mine too.

406
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,285
[Komi] I'm sad.

407
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:00,537
[Komi sighing]

408
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:05,209
[Komi] The c-closing ceremony

409
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,504
celebrating the end of school

410
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:13,342
is only a few days away.

411
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:17,930
We'll be put in new classes next week.

412
00:18:19,848 --> 00:18:22,976
I just feel sad that our time together

413
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:25,771
might be coming to an end.

414
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:32,027
I know how you feel.

415
00:18:35,614 --> 00:18:37,616
[dramatic music playing]

416
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,618
[inaudible]

417
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:43,288
[Hitohito] This year, it went by so fast.

418
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:52,589
[inaudible]

419
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:54,675
[Hitohito] First,
we made friends with Najimi

420
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:57,386
who says crazy things sometimes,

421
00:18:57,386 --> 00:19:01,265
but I also feel Najimi was the reason
we were all able to become friends.

422
00:19:01,765 --> 00:19:03,016
They took the lead.

423
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:04,810
[Komi grunting]

424
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:09,231
[Hitohito] After that
we made friends with Agari.

425
00:19:09,231 --> 00:19:12,192
Going out to eat
with her was an adventure.

426
00:19:12,901 --> 00:19:15,863
I hope we can go out to eat
with Agari again someday.

427
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:17,281
[Komi grunting]

428
00:19:18,615 --> 00:19:22,536
[Hitohito] Yamai and Nakanaka
always act like they're fighting,

429
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:25,205
but I think
they actually get along pretty well.

430
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:26,957
[Komi grunting emphatically]

431
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:31,545
Onemine and Otori are so stable.

432
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:34,214
Being around them
just somehow puts you at ease.

433
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:38,218
I feel like both of them
are really dependable people.

434
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:39,720
[Komi grunting]

435
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:44,433
I'm glad you made friends
with Kato and Sasaki on our school trip.

436
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,684
They seem nice.

437
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,102
[Komi grunting]

438
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,772
Somehow that trip made me happy too.

439
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:57,112
It's too bad we only got to help Sato
clean our classroom before school

440
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,530
just this last month.

441
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:00,240
[Komi grunting]

442
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:04,244
[Hitohito] I feel bad that she was
doing that all alone the whole year.

443
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:06,038
[Komi grunting]

444
00:20:06,663 --> 00:20:10,375
I also wanna try going out
with Maeda and Ushiroda someday.

445
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:11,919
[Komi grunting]

446
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:17,549
There was the school athletic festival,
a cultural festival.

447
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:20,177
We went shopping, to the water park.

448
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:22,387
We had that great Christmas party
and snowball fight!

449
00:20:22,387 --> 00:20:25,015
And went to a shrine on New Year's
to get our fortunes.

450
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:26,767
[Komi grunting]

451
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:40,030
[rain intensifying]

452
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:44,993
[Hitohito] The rain isn't stopping.

453
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:46,453
[Komi grunting]

454
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:51,375
[Hitohito] But it's going to stop someday.

455
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:53,335
[Komi grunting]

456
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:02,427
Uh, I was going
to use the rain stopping as symbolism

457
00:21:02,427 --> 00:21:04,846
and try to come up
with something witty to say,

458
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:07,391
but it was too hard.

459
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:08,892
[Komi gasping]

460
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:12,646
We've got a problem.

461
00:21:12,646 --> 00:21:13,814
[Komi grunting]

462
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:17,275
We've got a problem.

463
00:21:18,735 --> 00:21:20,404
[both sighing]

464
00:21:20,404 --> 00:21:22,531
You forgot your eraser unit!

465
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:25,784
- Huh? What? You two haven't gone home yet?
- [both shuddering]

466
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:28,287
[Najimi] Let's go home together!
You can share your umbrella.

467
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,872
Huh? Weren't you going somewhere?

468
00:21:30,872 --> 00:21:33,583
{\an8}- [Najimi] Hmm?
- [Hitohito] You wanted to leave early.

469
00:21:34,084 --> 00:21:35,502
[ending theme music playing]

470
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:39,047
Hey. How about we invite everyone out
after the closing ceremony?

471
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:40,299
Great idea!

472
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,801
Hey, Komi! You can invite everyone for us!

473
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:43,802
[Komi gasping]

474
00:21:45,303 --> 00:21:46,513
Oh, boy.

475
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,308
You don't have to force yourself.

476
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:50,434
[Komi shuddering]

477
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,442
[inaudible]

478
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:04,406
NOD

